<item>
            <title>[FLINK-31305] KafkaWriter doesn&apos;t wait for errors for in-flight records before completing flush</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-31305</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The KafkaWriter flushing needs to wait for all in-flight records to send successfully. This can be achieved by tracking requests and returning a response from the registered callback from the producer#send() logic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is potential for data loss since the checkpoint does not accurately reflect that all records have been sent successfully, to preserve at least once semantics.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
